docs.abstract: The virus outbreak supercharged a continuing shift in the markets, with a few giant companies now exerting the most influence over the direction of stocks since the tech boom.
docs.snippet: The virus outbreak supercharged a continuing shift in the markets, with a few giant companies now exerting the most influence over the direction of stocks since the tech boom.
docs.lead_paragraph: An economic downturn almost always favors giants like Microsoft, Apple and Amazon, the country’s three most valuable companies. But the demand for their shares has only been amplified by a crisis that seems almost tailor-made for their future success.

headline.main: Investors Bet Giant Companies Will Dominate After Crisis

docs.abstract: “I am an artist, not a Satanist,” the performance artist said after an online outcry prompted Microsoft to take down a video of her. It’s not the first time she’s faced the accusation.
docs.snippet: “I am an artist, not a Satanist,” the performance artist said after an online outcry prompted Microsoft to take down a video of her. It’s not the first time she’s faced the accusation.
docs.lead_paragraph: On April 10, Microsoft uploaded a film to its YouTube account about Marina Abramovic, the Serbian performance artist known for pushing her body to the limit.

headline.main: Marina Abramovic Just Wants Conspiracy Theorists to Let Her Be
headline.print_headline: She’s Never Met Satan. Isn’t Even a Fan. Honest.
